s_right/c_abf2fd2star  aDespite the impact of ideological rigidity, the primary challenge of heritage planning in Tehran and beyond lies not in the dominance of an inflexible Authorized Heritage Discourse, but rather in the absence of stable spatial-discursive and administrative structures. Solmaz Yadollahi maps the historical trajectory of conservation and urban heritage planning in Iran, depicting a discursive-spatial assemblage that tends to knock down its accumulated resources. This is in line with Katouzian's portrayal of Iran as a pick-axe society. Residing within this society, the studied assemblage strives to deconstruct the prevailing structures and usher in a fresh one, paradoxically perpetuating the very cycle it seeks to escape.  afunded by Vernetzungs- und Kompetenzstelle Open Access Brandenburg  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aArts. 4aArchitecture. 4aAssemblage. 4aCity. 4aConservation. 4aCultural History. 4aIran. 4aMemory Culture. 4aMuseum. 4aPlanning. 4aQualitative Social Research. 4aSpace. 4aTehran. 4aUrban Studies. 7aART / Museum Studies.2bisacsh  aArchitecture.  aAssemblage.  aCity.  aConservation.  aCultural History.  aIran.  aMemory Culture.  aMuseum.  aPlanning.  aQualitative Social Research.  aSpace.  aTehran.  aUrban Studies.2 aVernetzungs- und Kompetenzstelle Open Access Brandenburgefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2023z9783111318103oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2023 Englishz978311131903208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE CO